title: For Sale/Trade:  SOLD! - Winchester Model 70 30-06 - M70 Project Gun manufactured in 1970
postcontent:
I have a Winchester project gun that I am too busy to finish and I have reached the point that I am ready to go ahead and let it go to someone else who has the time to finish to bring it to completion. 
The rifle is a bolt action Winchester Model 70 originally chambered in 30-06.  The M70 was manufactured in 1970.  After buying it I mirror polished the bolt and refinished the stock (did a nice bright and shiny super grade type finish on it that looks really amazing).  I then subsequently discover the original standard profile 30-06 barrel attached to the Model 70 action had been previously damaged by a stuck round.  As you cannot return a gun you have started to modify it became a project gun. 
I purchased (2)x Winchester Model 70 donor barrels for the project (a 30-06 classic feather weight barrel and a .222 Remington barrel) to replace the damage barrel.  The bad 30-06 barrel has been removed.  The Winchester Model 70 30-06 featherweight donor barrel has been installed in its place however the head spacing has not been tested since the barrel was swapped and I believe the barrel is going to need to be turned to properly mate with the action.  (Head spacing must be verified before it would be safe to shoot.) 
The rifle has been fully disassembled, cleaned, and all necessary replacement parts have been purchased, and reassembled.   I will include all the original parts and the replacement parts as part of the project package.  (See Photos).  Please email with any questions.Buyer / Trade Partner Requirement: Anyone I conduct a transaction with must have valid Florida Driver's license / ID.  I will not sell to anyone under 21.  I prefer working individuals that are CWP holders.  Individuals I work with must be willing to fillout paperwork and sign a bill of sale. I vet everyone I sell to or trade with so do not contact me if you are a felon.  I will check criminal history and if you have a record it will come out so do not bother trying to lie your way through a transaction. I guarantee trying to circumvent any of these requirements will cause the transaction to fail and ultimately waste everyone's time.  If you are looking for a backroom undocumented or non-registered sale you will want to find someone else to work with.

postcontent: The revolutionary Binary Firing System will be appreciated by three gun competitors, tactical shooters, and recreational enthusiasts. It features a three position selector that allows the user to switch from Mode 1 for Safe, Mode 2 for traditional Semiautomatic Mode, or Mode 3 for Binary Mode. In Binary Mode, the firearm will discharge one round with every function of the trigger whether a pull or a release. A user can negate the round that would otherwise be fired during the release function by simply moving the selector back to Mode 2 and then safely releasing the trigger. Features: - Easy drop in installation.
